cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper deals with medical image registration using CNNs, which is a subfield of computer vision. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes an end-to-end registration framework using a CNN-based mutual information neural estimator, which involves machine learning techniques. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper uses deep learning techniques to achieve accurate medical image registration, which falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses mutual information as a metric for evaluating the registration outputs, which is a concept from information theory. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper proposes a weakly supervised network combining mutual information with the Dice similarity coefficients (DSC) loss, which involves neural network training techniques.
